  Your small E0.5 run suggests exactly this pattern:

  - B wm2 beat B wm10
  - C ep1 beat C ep10
  - D sem1 beat D sem4

  That is a strong hint that:

  - memory is useful
  - but memory must be selective
  - scaling memory naively can reduce accuracy

  That is why E0.5 matters. It turns the paper from:

