  The current data supports these exact claims:

  - Memory materially improves multi-turn enterprise Text-to-SQL accuracy.
  - Memory does not matter much for simple one-turn tasks.
  - Working memory provides most of the gain.
  - More memory is not always better.
  - The best operating point looks like small working memory plus selective episodic retrieval.

